                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: The id refers to Freud’s term for our inborn basic drives. Morals are learned from society. LO 3.3 Explain how the development of personality and morality and socialization into emotions are part of how “society makes us human.”"
                },
                "answer_2": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Eros refers to a Greek God of love, not one of Freud’s personality parts. LO 3.3 Explain how the development of personality and morality and socialization into emotions are part of how “society makes us human.”"
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: The ego is the balancing force between the id and the demands of society that suppress it. Morals are part of those social demands. LO 3.3 Explain how the development of personality and morality and socialization into emotions are part of how “society makes us human.”"
